<P>PROSE ON SEVERAL OCCASIONS; ACCOMPANIED WITH SOME PIECES IN VERSE.</P>
<P>BY <HI>GEORGE COLMAN.</HI></P>
<P>VOL. I.</P>
<P><Q><L>&mdash;Sen me tranquilla &s;enectus</L>
<L>Expectat, &s;en Mors atris circumvolat alis,</L>
<L>Dives, inops, Romae, &s;eu fors ita ju&s;&s;erit, exul,</L>
<L>Qui&s;quis erit vitae, &s;cribam, color.&mdash;</L>
<BIBL>HOR.</BIBL></Q>IMITATED.
<Q><L>Whether Old Age a tranquil evening brings,</L>
<L>Or Death &s;ails round me with his Raven Wings;</L>
<L>Rich, poor; at Rome, or London; well, or ill;</L>
<L>Whate'er my fortunes, write I mu&s;t and will.</L></Q></P>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI> PRINTED FOR T. CADEL, IN THE STRAND. MDCCLXXXVII.</P>
</DIV1>
