<ITEM>P. 178. THE GENTLEMAN, NO. III. ON the pre&s;ent STATE OF LEARNING. ON PURITY OF STYLE. On the imitation of Living Authors, and neglect of the works of Decea&s;ed Writers. Of fal&s;e Ornaments. Of <HI>Idiom.</HI> Proper u&s;e of Grammars and Dictionaries.</ITEM>
